Wash and dry produce. Halve, peel, and finely dice @yellow onion{1}(peeled and finely diced). Drain and rinse @chickpeas{13.4%ounce}.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon} in a #large pot{} over medium-high heat. Add @Italian chicken sausage mix{9%ounce} and cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Add onion; cook, stirring occasionally, until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Stir in @tomato paste{1.5%ounce} and @Italian seasoning{1%tablespoon}; cook, stirring, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir 2 1/2 cups @water{2 1/2%cups}, @chicken stock concentrate{2%units}, chickpeas, and a big pinch of @salt{pinch} into pot. Cover and bring to a boil, then reduce heat to medium. Simmer, covered, for ~{7%minutes}.

Once soup has simmered for 7 minutes, uncover pot and stir in @baby spinach{5%ounce}. Simmer, uncovered, until spinach has wilted, ~{2-3%minutes} more. Season generously with @salt{} and @pepper{} to taste.

Divide soup between bowls and serve.